snippet.textDisplay: I wanna say something serious for once and sorry if my english isn't perfect. I really admire how Felix grew up to become an adult. I remember how he was years ago and then look at videos like this and I'm like "wow". I'm not saying this because he's PewDiePie, let's be clear. I'm not even a huge fan to be honest. I'm just a casual viewer. But seeing a boy like he was becoming an adult is moving for me. Maybe it's because I'm 26 and I don't really know what to do in my life yet, but this is really inspiring to me. And that's beacuse at the end of the day Felix's just a regular human being, and to this I can relate a lot. Anyway, all I wanted to say is, "Felix, be proud of yourself, because you and all the people like you, are an inspiration to people like me, who really struggle to grow up."

snippet.textDisplay: Unfortunately these comments originate from an unhealthy mindset of "eat the rich", which is a "movement" built on jealousy and hatred for the "wealthy". These types of people believe "net worth" is liquid currency (cash, ready to spend) sitting in said "rich" persons bank account collecting dust. These are also the same people that flame celebrities for donating "too little" to charities and proceed to rant on about how the celebrity's "net worth" could support an entire city for a year. What they don't know, is that person doesn't make that much money, net worth is the value of all your property plus your income (so if you own the company "Amazon", that company's value will be added to your net worth). Another strong note, all of the revenue the company makes gets redistributed into the company to pay employees, pay very big bills, fund very big projects, and ultimately keep the company running and thousands of people employed.
